{
  "stem": "12904.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she told me in 1978, when I was back visiting, that I should not tell anyone, any of the neighbors or the store nearby, grocery store, I should not tell them who I was or why I had left Germany.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had told her, 33 years after the war ended, how can you still be afraid?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And she said, it's just not a good idea to tell anyone that you're Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I didn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And she told me not to tell them who my father was.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said, nobody would know him any more.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You know, at that point.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "During the Holocaust?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's sister-- I have a picture of her that you can get later-- was married to an ophthalmologist, and he did not want to leave even though they did have affidavits.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had a son in Shanghai, and my uncle did not want to go to Shanghai.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we had given them an affidavit, and some relatives, his brother in Philadelphia, gave them an affidavit.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, part of it, they did not get out because we did not allow-- under President Roosevelt-- the State Department did not allow, in the early '40s, for any more Jews to come in, any more refugees.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we found that out much later.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I didn't know why they didn't come.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have some last letters from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But anyway, by aunt was married to this Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Kaufman, Eugene Kaufman, an ophthalmologist.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were eventually both deported, after moving, I don't know, X number of times.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And after they had stolen his, apparently, his whole practice-- medical practice-- had been stolen or vandalized, they were deported first to Theresienstadt, which is called Theresien in Polish.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he apparently died there.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
